Join us January 22nd at Roadhouse Cinemas Colorado Springs @sixfeetunderhorrorfest as we pay homage to horror LEGEND Linnea Quigley, who will be IN ATTENDANCE!

The festivities will begin with a meet and greet in the theater lobby starting at 1:00 PM. ANYONE is welcome, but VIP ticketholders will be guaranteed express access, a signed poster, one signed personal memorabilia item, a selfie with Linnea, and some surely unforgettable discussion and facetime with this horror GODDESS!

The cinematic portion of the event will begin at 4:00 PM with screenings of Graduation Day (1981) and Return of the Living Dead (1985), including Q&A’s hosted by Ms. Quigley. 

Sprinkled throughout the event, once again, will be a collection of horror short films and our ever beloved horror trivia, with phenomenal prizes for our winners!

Don’t miss this incredible opportunity! Get those tickets today! sixfeetunderhorrorfest.com

We are beyond excited for our next two blu-ray titles. They are FULL of special features and have rad artwork by Earl Kess. Welcome LINNEA QUIGLEY’S HORROR WORKOUT (1990) & GET MY GUN (2017) to the Terror Vision Home Video lineup! In addition to the rad blu-ray release of Horror Workout, we also found the original music elements so we were able to do a release of the score on vinyl and cassette. Additionally, there’s a bundle with the blu, LP, tee and enamel pin. So tons of fun stuff! If you’re in the Terror Vision Video Club, you’ll automatically receive these blu’s on/around May 1st. Join the Video Club today if you haven’t. It’s a no-brainer. If you’re in the Terror Vision Record or Cassette Club, you’ll receive your format release in July. Cassette Club spots are full but you can join the Record Club to receive this title and more. Grab all of these goodies at terror-vision.com. xoxo

Scream Queen LINNEA QUIGLEY, prominent and influential in horror films such as Night of the Demons and Return of the Living Dead, will be present for a one hour photo and autograph session to raise funds for her animal sanctuary Moulin Rouge. In honor of Linnea’s appearance, Ricasso's Antiques & Cool Collectibles will be donating a portion of the profits to her animal sanctuary. Stop by on Saturday July 22nd to help out a worthy cause. 😎
